ability.weaponmaster.buster.confession: Hello there fellow dev! Desian here. You're either reading this making an addon mod (I'm sorry) or making a resource pack (I'm *really* sorry). Either way, I'm not here to help you! (again, sorry). But look, I need to tell you about something about buster. Originally, what would eventually become resist and smokescreen was a collection of single potion effect abilities, labelled pot_resist, post_speed and pot_invis. Now, obviously, being the funny jokester I am, I also made a pot_buster. It didn't *do* anything but it was very funny for a bit. Now, like any self-respecting programmer I don't know when to drop a joke, so it got a really basic implementation, you literally just jumped up and anyone you hit got knocked down. It sucked and I fully intended to remove it. Anyway, a lot of things got shuffled around during testing, including the removal of the pot_ abilities in favour of the more flavourful variants we have now. This brought a little too much attention to buster and insted of doing the smart thing of going 'yeah gimme a sec i'll remove that' I went along with Forset and actually remade it into a proper ability! This took weeks! It ***STILL*** has netcode issues! Anyway, absolutely no part of the original joke exists in the final build otherwise so I kinda felt like I *needed* to document it in some form, y'know?
